The paper deals with wireless device-to-device (D2D) caching in cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the optimization of caching strategies, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper uses analytical modeling to characterize the average download delay, which can be classified under signal processing (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the categorization of mobile terminals based on their file preferences, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG).
